      "body" : "<i>&quot;... 3rd party website which has been confirmed by JAVA community ...&quot;</i> - This doesn&#39;t mean anything.  The key thing is to download the distro from the &gt;&gt;distro vendor&#39;s website&lt;&lt;.  You can validate that by checking the website&#39;s certificate in your web browser.  There are a number of reputable 3rd-party Java vendors / distributors.  But the &quot;Java community&quot; is not a thing that can &quot;confirm&quot; a website or a vendor.  (Anymore that the &quot;Java community&quot; can &quot;confirm&quot; Oracle or its websites.)"
